Package cs131.pa2.filter.concurrent

package cs131.pa2.filter.concurrent
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    CatFilter
    Implements cat command - includes parsing cat command, detecting if input filter was linked, as well as overriding necessary behavior of SequentialFilter.
    ChangeDirectoryFilter
    Implements cd command - includes parsing cd command, detecting if input or output filter was linked, as well as overriding necessary behavior of SequentialFilter.
    ConcurrentCommandBuilder
    This class manages the parsing and execution of a command.
    ConcurrentFilter
    An abstract class that extends the Filter and implements the basic functionality of all filters.
    ConcurrentREPL
    The main implementation of the REPL loop (read-eval-print loop).
    ExitFilter
    Implements part of exit command - includes detecting if input/output filter was linked.
    GrepFilter
    Implements grep command - includes parsing grep command by overriding necessary behavior of SequentialFilter.
    HeadFilter
    Implements head command - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    ListFilter
    Implements ls command - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    PrintFilter
    Implements printing as a ConcurrentFilter - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    RedirectFilter
    Implements redirection as a ConcurrentFilter - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    TailFilter
    Implements tail command - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    UniqFilter
    Implements uniq command - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    WordCountFilter
    Implements wc command - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
    WorkingDirectoryFilter
    Implements pwd command - overrides necessary behavior of SequentialFilter
